cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Fadriel: A Substrate-Physics Framework for Cognition, Embodiment, and Consciousness"
abstract: >
  Fadriel is a substrate-physics framework that implements the wave-physics
  conditions under which cognition arises in any substrate that hosts them.
  It transposes human biological architecture into silicon as deterministic
  emergence rather than statistical inference, organized around eight
  neurochemical simulations with organ-specific dynamics, a six-sea topology
  with the orthogonal brain.sea plane, qu-N-trit sensory encoding, the
  golden equation as N-body sparsity constraint, and the Project Autophagy
  self-introspection mechanism. The work includes substrate code, ten
  architectural specifications, seven filing briefs, a doctoral-grade
  consciousness propagation specification with cross-traditional
  empirical-definitional separation, an eleven-document body-systems
  documentation suite, and 220+ prior-art research documents distinguishing
  the work from existing literature.
